.TH GOLF 2gg $VERSION $DATE Development Tools
.SH NAME
install-binary \- Golf documentation (download-and-build)
.SH DESCRIPTION

.LP
.B INSTALLING AND MANAGING GOLF WITH LINUX PACKAGING TOOLS
.LP


.LP
.B UBUNTU
.LP

For Ubuntu (versions 20 through 24, as well as upcoming releases), use \fBGolf's Launchpad PPA\fP:

.RS 4
.EX

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:golf-lang/golf
sudo apt update

.EE
.RE

After that you can install and manage Golf with the standard apt package tools, for instance to install it:

.RS 4
.EX

sudo apt install golf

.EE
.RE


.LP
.B ARCH LINUX
.LP

For Arch Linux, Golf's AUR page is \fBhttps://aur.archlinux.org/packages/golf\fP. To download, build package, and install from it (answer Yes to proceed):

.RS 4
.EX

git clone https://aur.archlinux.org/golf.git
cd golf
makepkg -sirc

.EE
.RE

Please note that binary distributions for other Linux distros should be available soon. In any case, you can always \fBinstall from source\fP.
